 any files the agent touched during the session, and everything was committed — consider the session ended.\\n\\nI think this is a solid signal, but with some nuances to think through:\\n\\n**What I like:**\\n- It fills a real gap — right now there's no great way to detect \\\"user is done with agent work and is context-switching.\\\" A stash is a strong intent signal that the user is moving on.\\n- It's a natural complement to the existing commit-based condensation. Commit = \\\"I'm keeping this work.\\\" Stash = \\\"I'm shelving this work.\\\"\\n- If the stash contains *none* of the agent-touched files, it means the user committed all the agent's work already and is just stashing their own unrelated changes — a clean end signal.\\n\\n**Things to consider:**\\n\\n1. **Stash + pop workflow:** Users often do `stash → pull → pop`. That's not \\\"ending\\\" the session — it's a brief interruption (similar to the existing shadow branch migration for pull/rebase). You'd need to distinguish \\\"stash as shelving\\\" from \\\"stash as momentary parking.\\\" One way: only treat it as session-ended if the stash persists (i.e., don't act on the stash itself, act on the *next session start* when you see a stash exists but no agent files are dirty).\\n\\n2. **Detection mechanism:** There's no `post-stash` git hook. So you'd need to detect this lazily — e.g., at next `SessionStart` or `TurnStart`, check if the working tree is clean and the previous session's files were stashed/committed. This fits well with the existing pattern of checking state at session boundaries.\\n\\n3. **Partial stash (`git stash push -p` or `git stash push -- <files>`):** The user might stash only some files. If they stash non-agent files and leave agent files unstaged, that's not a clear \\\"end\\\" signal.\\n\\n4. **`git stash` vs `git stash --keep-index`:** Different intentions. `--keep-index` is often used before running tests, not for context-switching.\\n\\n**My suggestion:** Rather than triggering on the stash event itself, make it a condition checked at session start:\\n\\n> At `SessionStart`: if the previous session has no uncommitted agent-touched files in the working tree (either committed or stashed away), and the session is `IDLE`/`ENDED`, auto-end it and clean up.\\n\\nThis sidesteps the stash-then-pop problem (because if they pop before the next session, the files are back) and works without needing a stash hook. It's essentially: \\\"if by the time a new session starts, all previous agent work is accounted for, close out the old session.\\\"\\n\\nWant me to look at the existing session start logic to see where this check would fit?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":945,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":15776,\"output_tokens\":743,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":945,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYmnTCkPoarPzdHZP2Eiy\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"376026c3-5cde-4195-b052-7871eb457a18\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T11:56:45.361Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"376026c3-5cde-4195-b052-7871eb457a18\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"57ad503f-9eba-494b-bba0-e3b4e73f710e\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/use-changelog-for-release-notes\",\"slug\":\"modular-tickling-trinket\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"8c1a8ef2-6643-4eaf-af91-1bcf2d407aef\",\"toolUseID\":\"8c1a8ef2-6643-4eaf-af91-1bcf2d407aef\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T11:56:45.384Z\",\"uuid\":\"d42292f1-e149-4bb4-b6a5-b1462829f8d8\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"