:\"faaf1353-3131-4e62-b023-98578e29cac0\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"cccc455a-17d3-48f9-8422-01996ea70e79\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"docs/architecture/stash-aware-session-end.md\":{\"backupFileName\":null,\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-06T16:15:38.977Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T16:14:56.515Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"7c5b585d-a26a-4553-b61a-3a8f252f1d50\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"57ad503f-9eba-494b-bba0-e3b4e73f710e\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/carry-forward-improvements\",\"slug\":\"modular-tickling-trinket\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01BDDGWjrxwJ5eUCC3AFTfGH\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01LFuqeGEfxyBhYDLD1PVFan\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/stash-aware-session-end.md\",\"content\":\"# Stash-Aware Session End Detection\\n\\n## Status: Design\\n\\n## Problem Statement\\n\\nWhen an agent modifies files during a session and the user commits only some of them,\\nthe remaining uncommitted changes enter carry-forward. If the user then **discards**\\nthose remaining changes (e.g., `git checkout -- <file>`, `git restore`), the system\\nhas no way to detect this. The carry-forward lingers until the 7-day stale timeout or\\nuntil a new session absorbs it (Option B in `hunk-level-carry-forward.md`).\\n\\nThere is a detectable state that signals the session is done:\\n\\n1. `carry_forward_files` exist (agent touched files that weren't committed)\\n2. Working tree is clean (no unstaged/staged changes for those files)\\n3. Stash is empty, OR stash entries don't contain those files\\n\\nIf all three conditions hold, the remaining agent changes are gone — the user either\\ndiscarded them or they were otherwise resolved. The session should be marked as fully\\ncondensed.\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Detection Logic\\n\\nAfter a commit triggers carry-forward computation (PostCommit), or at session start:\\n\\n```\\nremaining = filesWithRemainingAgentChanges()\\n\\nif len(remaining) > 0:\\n    for each file in remaining:\\n        if file is dirty in working tree (unstaged or staged):\\n            keep carry-forward alive, return\\n\\n    # Working tree is clean for all remaining files.\\n    # Check stash.\\n\\n    if stashContainsCarryForwardFiles(remaining):\\n        keep carry-forward alive, return\\n\\n    # Changes are gone — user discarded them.\\n    mark FullyCondensed = true\\n    delete shadow branch\\n```\\n\\n### Stash Inspection via Reflog\\n\\nThe stash reflog lives at `.git/logs/refs/stash`. It is shared across all worktrees,\\nso entries must be filtered to the relevant worktree.\\n\\n#### Worktree Discrimination\\n\\nEach stash entry's first parent is the HEAD commit at stash time. Different worktrees\\nare on different branches at different commits, so the parent commit acts as a natural\\nworktree discriminator. The only ambiguity is if two worktrees are checked out at the\\nexact same commit, which git actively warns against.\\n\\n#### Algorithm: `stashContainsCarryForwardFiles`\\n\\n```\\nfunc stashContainsCarryForwardFiles(remainingFiles []string, sessionBaseCommit hash) bool:\\n    1. Check if .git/logs/refs/stash exists\\n       - Does not exist -> return false (no stash, no overlap)\\n\\n    2. Parse stash reflog entries from .git/logs/refs/stash\\n\\n    3. For each stash entry:\\n       a. Resolve the stash commit\\n       b. Check first parent commit\\n          - If parent does not match sessionBaseCommit or current HEAD\\n            of this worktree -> skip (stash is from a different worktree)\\n       c. Diff the stash commit tree against its parent to get stashed files\\n       d. Intersect stashed files with remainingFiles\\n          - If overlap -> return true\\n\\n    4. No matching stash entry found -> return false\\n```\\n\\n#### Why Parent Commit Matching Works\\n\\n- Worktree A is on commit `abc1234` (branch `feature-x`)\\n- Worktree B is on commit `def5678` (branch `feature-y`)\\n- User runs `git stash` from worktree A\\n- Stash entry's parent = `abc1234`\\n- When checking worktree B's session (base commit `def5678`), the parent doesn't match\\n  -> stash entry is skipped\\n- No false positives across worktrees\\n\\n### When to Run the Check\\n\\n**PostCommit** is the natural trigger. After condensation computes remaining files,\\nif remaining files exist but none are dirty in the working tree, run the stash check.\\nThis catches the sequence:\\n\\n1. Agent touches A, B, C\\n2. User commits A, B -> carry-forward has C\\n3. User runs `git checkout -- C` (discards C)\\n4. PostCommit (from step 2) or next hook invocation detects: C not dirty, not stashed\\n5. Session marked fully condensed\\n\\n**Session start** is a secondary trigger. Before creating a new shadow branch, check\\nif old sessions' carry-forward files are gone. This catches cases where the user\\ndiscards changes without making another commit (no PostCommit fires).\\n\\n### Edge Cases\\n\\n#### User stashes then pops\\n\\n- User stashes agent files -> stash check finds overlap -> carry-forward stays alive\\n- User pops stash -> files are dirty again -> carry-forward stays alive (working tree check)\\n- User eventually commits or discards -> normal flow\\n\\n#### User stashes unrelated files\\n\\n- Stash entry exists but contains files not in `carry_forward_files`\\n- No overlap -> correctly treated as \\\"no stash\\\" for this session\\n\\n#### Multiple stash entries\\n\\n- User may have several stash entries from different points in time\\n- All entries are checked; only entries whose parent matches the session's base commit\\n  or current HEAD are considered\\n\\n#### Stash with `--include-untracked` or `--all`\\n\\n- These create a third parent commit on the stash entry containing untracked/ignored files\\n- The file overlap check should include files from all parents of the stash commit\\n- In practice, untracked files are unlikely to overlap with `carry_forward_files` (which\\n  are tracked files the agent modified)\\n\\n#### Working tree clean but files staged\\n\\n- If a carry-forward file is staged (in the index) but not yet committed, `git status`\\n  shows it as staged\\n- The \\\"is file dirty\\\" check should include both unstaged AND staged changes\\n- Staged files mean the user intends to commit -> keep carry-forward alive\\n\\n## Relationship to Carry-Forward Options\\n\\nThis check is **orthogonal** to both Option A (hunk-level) and Option B (session-bounded)\\nfrom `hunk-level-carry-forward.md`. It can be combined with either:\\n\\n- **With Option A**: After diff3 determines remaining hunks, if those hunks are no longer\\n  in the working tree or stash, mark as consumed.\\n- **With Option B**: At session start cleanup, additionally check if old sessions' files\\n  were discarded (not just absorbed by the new session).\\n- **Standalone**: Even without Option A or B, this improves the current file-level\\n  carry-forward by detecting discarded changes earlier than the 7-day timeout.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | PostCommit: add stash-aware check after computing remaining files |\\n| `strategy/common.go` or new `strategy/stash.go` | `stashContainsCarryForwardFiles()` implementation |\\n| `session/state.go` | No changes needed (uses existing `carry_forward_files`) |\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":377,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":30031,\"output_tokens\":1731,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":377,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"infe